  "description": "Assonance is the repetition of vowel sounds within nearby words, independent of consonants. Unlike [rhyme](./rhyme.md), which matches both vowel and following consonant sounds, assonance matches vowels alone: *lake/fate*, *deep/leen*, *hold/bone*.",
